              <tr><td colspan="3"><hr width="100%" size="1"></td></tr>
              <tr><td colspan="3"><b>Description</b><br>
The smallest zone in the game. It contains no monsters and no NPC's. It's a large circle zone, with a tall circle wall in it. There is an opening in the circle wall inside.  Once you go inside the circle wall, you enter the PVP arena. There are about 8 pillars inside this zone that you can get up real high on if you use levitate because they are slanted. In the center there is a throne, many events are held in the arena. Once you enter the arena, anyone can attack and kill you, with no lose of experience. Be carefull that if you get a DOT on you, DO NOT go outside the arena, if you die out there you will lose experience. You can bind to this area also, good place to bind for hunting around that area. The entrance to it is located in Lake Rathe, to the left of the
barbarian huts.
<br><br>
This zone can be fun if you have levitate.  You can even go over the walls into "unmapped places". I wouldn't suggest going out there because you may fall or get stuck or something and lose you corpse. It's fun to gather guilds and friends there for friendly duels and testing.
<br><br>
Pets are not allowed inside the arena, they will kill themselves the second you enter. Don't go AFK inside the arena because someone may come along and kill you. Keep in mind that you're not IN the arena the second you enter the zone, the actual arena is in the large circle walls inside the arena zone. You can enter in and out through a large entrance. This zone counts as outdoors, so no indoor/dungen spells are
allowed.
<br><br>
Not much to this zone, just an arena and bind point, it could use a merchant or a bank for convenience, but that wont happen.
<br><br>
Submitted By: Nadger</td></tr>
