  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C" class="c1">Jayge - as indicated "the arena" is NOT when you zone in. Walk into the Arena itself, summon a pet. Watch it die the same tick.<br>
Reason?<br>
Since "there are no NPC's" in this zone - ie no mobs, guards, merchants, etc, Verant didn't feel any need to include NPC pathing points inside the PvP area proper.<br>
So the instant a pet enters the arena itself, it doesn't know how to get to you (it's an npc after all) and it suicides.<br><br></td></tr>
